
1. This country is almost directly in the center of Africa, and is Africa's
2nd largest country to date, with Algeria being the largest.
2. One can find the United Nation's largest peacekeeping mission in the
world in the Democratic Republic of the Congo. It over 20 thousand soldiers
from about 50 other countries.
3. Due to being a landlocked country almost directly in the center of
Africa, this nation borders nine others - Angola, Burundi, Rwanda, the
Central African Republic, the Republic of the Congo, South Sudan,
Tanzania, Uganda, and Zambia.
4. There are over 200 ethnic groups with approximately 250 spoken languages in
this country.
5. Despite being rich in minerals - tungsten, tin, tantalum, and gold - the
Democratic Republic of the Congo still has an extremely poor population.
